<section class="component  ">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
    <h2 class="visible">Community Relations</h2>
  
    <figure class="_image captioned-image image-right-third">
  <img src="https://pga.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/57/2018/04/PackthePav_13-1090x727.jpg" alt="Sparky high-fiving children at basketball game">
  </figure>
  
  <p>The Office of Community Relations works to build and maintain relationships between UIC and its neighboring communities. The office works with local civic, corporate and community organizations in addition to supporting internal constituents. The Office of Community Relations serves as a platform for internal and external stakeholders to exchange ideas. Community Relations promotes local and regional economic development through raising awareness about opportunities. Community Relations works to engage all partners in helping UIC pursue its mission as a leading urban public research institution and the University of Illinois<em> for</em> Chicago.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Maintaining and cultivating community partnerships</li>
<li>Promoting local and regional economic development</li>
<li>Coordinating business engagement</li>
<li>Faculty expert facilitation for external constituents</li>
<li>Special programs and initiatives</li>
<li>Community calendar</li>
<li>Community newsletter</li>
<li>Advising senior leadership on community issues</li>
</ul>
<p>To partner with Community Relations, email <a href="mailto:community@uic.edu">community@uic.edu</a>.</p>



  
</div>

  
</section>

    
    
      

<section class="component  ">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
    <h2 class="visible">Digital Communications</h2>
  
    <figure class="_image captioned-image image-right-third">
  <img src="https://pga.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/57/2018/04/RedMobileScreenshot.png" alt="screenshot of red.uic.edu website">
  </figure>
  
  <p class="p2">Responsible for UIC’s digital communications strategy and branding. The team manages the university’s home page, <a href="http://uic.edu">uic.edu</a>, as well as other top-level pages.</p>
<p>In partnership with ACCC, Digital Communications manages and supports the Red WordPress multisite, the primary resource for creating and managing UIC websites.</p>
<p class="p3"><b>Resources provided:</b></p>
<ul>
<li class="p4">RED WordPress multisite: site creation, launch, support and training</li>
<li class="p5">Support and guidance for best practices of design, content, navigation and accessibility on UIC websites</li>
</ul>



      <ul class="link-list">
  <li class="_item">
    <a href="https://red.uic.edu" target="_blank">
      Learn more about the Red WordPress Multisite
    </a>
  </li>
</ul>
  
</div>

  
</section>

    
    
      

<section class="component  ">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
    <h2 class="visible">Government Relations</h2>
  
    <figure class="_image captioned-image image-left-third">
  <img src="https://pga.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/57/2018/04/rsz_student_lobby_day235-1-1090x727.jpg" alt="students, staff, faculty, alumni, and other university supporters at Lobby Day 2018">
  </figure>
  
  <p>The UIC Office of Public and Government Affairs, in collaboration with the University of Illinois Office of Government Relations, supports the advo­cacy efforts of the UI President and UIC Chancellor at the local, county, state, and federal levels. The office provides support for legislative efforts and strengthens relationships with government stakeholders. The office also collaborates with Illinois Connec­tion, the University of Illinois Alumni Alliance&#8217;s legislative advocacy network, on a range of advocacy-related projects.</p>
<p>UIC, located on the near west side of Chicago, works closely with Mayor <a href="https://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/mayor.html">Rahm Emanuel</a> and its four representatives on the Chicago City Council – 27<sup>th</sup> Ward Alderman <a href="https://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/about/wards/27.html">Walter Burnett</a>, 28<sup>th</sup> Ward Alderman <a href="https://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/about/wards/28.html">Jason Ervin</a>, 25<sup>th</sup> Ward Alderman <a href="https://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/about/wards/25.html">Daniel Solis</a>, and 11<sup>th</sup> Ward Alderman <a href="https://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/about/wards/11.html">Patrick Thompson</a>. The Mayor and aldermen work with UIC on community and economic development initiatives that benefit the city and its residents.</p>
<p>At the county level, UIC regularly collaborates with the office of Cook County Board President <a href="https://www.cookcountyil.gov/person/toni-preckwinkle">Toni Preckwinkle</a>. The university is located within Cook County’s 2<sup>nd</sup> District, represented by Commissioner <a href="https://www.cookcountyil.gov/person/dennis-deer">Dennis Deer</a>.</p>
<p>As an urban-serving university situated in Illinois’ largest city, UIC works closely with its partners in Illinois state government including Governor <a href="https://www2.illinois.gov/gov/Pages/default.aspx">Bruce Rauner</a>. UIC is represented in the Illinois General Assembly by Representative <a href="http://www.ilga.gov/house/rep.asp?MemberID=2378">Arthur Turner</a>, 9<sup>th</sup> District and Senator <a href="http://www.ilga.gov/senate/Senator.asp?MemberID=2418">Patricia Van Pelt</a> , 5<sup>th</sup> District. The UI System budget and higher education funding is a priority for our legislators.</p>
<p>Senator <a href="https://www.durbin.senate.gov/">Dick Durbin</a>, Senator <a href="https://www.duckworth.senate.gov/">Tammy Duckworth</a>, and Congressman <a href="https://davis.house.gov/">Danny Davis</a>, Illinois 7<sup>th</sup> District represent UIC at the federal level. UIC works with these legislators to provide resources that advance research and scholarship.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Building support for bills, amendments, and ordinances in the Illinois General Assembly, Chicago City Council, and Cook County Board of Commissioners</li>
<li>Monitoring UI and UIC legislation in the Illinois General Assembly, Chicago City Council, and Cook County Board of Commissioners and providing updates to UIC leadership, colleges and units</li>
<li>Building support and advocates for UIC budget-related line items in Springfield</li>
<li>Engaging legislative caucuses within city, state, federal government</li>
<li>Collaborating with government agencies on higher education initiatives</li>
</ul>
<p>To connect with Government Relations, email <a href="mailto:govt@uic.edu">govt@uic.edu</a>.</p>



  
</div>

  
</section>

    
    
      

<section class="component  ">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
    <h2 class="visible">Marketing and Brand Management</h2>
  
    <figure class="_image captioned-image image-right-third">
  <img src="https://pga.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/57/2018/04/brand-binder_022517_Page_001.jpg" alt="cover of style guide">
  </figure>
  
  <p class="p1"><span class="s1">Marketing and Brand Management serves the University of Illinois at Chicago by providing resources and guidance to help ensure that the institution’s marketing and communications initiatives are aligned with the university’s brand and identity. Maintaining consistency in messaging and design across the university reinforces the UIC brand overall.</span></p>
<p><b>Resources provided:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>University licensing and filming programs</li>
<li>Style guide including logos and templates for PPT and stationery</li>
<li>Photo and video gallery</li>
<li>Marketing consultation including development of marketing and communications plans, design of print collateral, development of messaging</li>
<li>Campus banner reservations</li>
<li>Branding and text treatment design</li>
</ul>



      <ul class="link-list">
  <li class="_item">
    <a href="http://marketing.uic.edu" target="_blank">
      Visit the Marketing and Brand Management website
    </a>
  </li>
</ul>
  
</div>

  
</section>

    
    
      

<section class="component  ">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
    <h2 class="visible">Public Affairs</h2>
  
    <figure class="_image captioned-image image-right-half">
  <img src="https://pga.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/57/2018/04/uicnewsuictoday1-1090x809.jpg" alt="cover of recent U I C news">
  </figure>
  
  <p>The Office of Public Affairs is an information source and public portal to the campus. Working with media in all its forms, the office broadens public awareness and understanding of UIC, its mission and the achievements of its faculty and students. In addition to outreach through the media, Public Affairs manages UIC’s own news and information properties including UIC today; UIC News, the award-winning print and online campus newspaper; audio and video productions; and social media channels.</p>
<p><strong>Resources provided:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Disseminate news and information about UIC to internal and external stakeholders</li>
<li>Provide strategic leadership for media and public relations</li>
<li><a href="https://today.uic.edu/experts-guide">Experts guide</a> for the media</li>
<li>Manage the university’s primary social media channels, including <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/thisisUIC">YouTube</a>; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/uic.edu">Facebook</a>; <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/edu/school?id=18319&amp;trk=edu-ca-frm-cncl">LinkedIn</a>; <a href="https://twitter.com/thisisUIC">Twitter</a>; and the <a href="http://uicscience.tumblr.com/">UIC Science blog</a></li>
<li>Support units in cross-campus <a href="https://today.uic.edu/contact/communicating-on-campus">internal communications</a></li>
<li>Guidance on <a href="https://today.uic.edu/contact/communicating-on-campus/photo-video-policies">photo and video policies</a></li>
<li>Serve the campus administration and colleges in crisis and emergency communications</li>
</ul>



      <ul class="link-list">
  <li class="_item">
    <a href="http://today.uic.edu/" target="_blank">
      Visit UIC today for up-to-the-minute news and information
    </a>
  </li>
</ul>
  
</div>

  
</section>

    

